## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="0ae5e-139">L'esempio seguente crea una grammatica che riconosce la frase "è un nazione che ha vinto del mondo FIFA" seguito dal nome di un paese ha vinto del mondo FIFA.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="0ae5e-139">The following example creates a grammar that recognizes the phrase "A nation that has won the World Cup is" followed by the name of a country that has won the World Cup.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="0ae5e-140">Nell'esempio viene creata una regola pubblica denominata `WorldCupWinner`.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="0ae5e-140">The example creates a public rule named `WorldCupWinner`.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="0ae5e-141">L'esempio crea quindi due <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule> oggetti `ruleEurope` e `ruleSAmerica`, passando un <xref:System.String> per l'identificatore della regola e un <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsElement> matrice contenente un <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf> oggetto.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="0ae5e-141">The example then creates two <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule> objects, `ruleEurope` and  `ruleSAmerica`, passing in a <xref:System.String> for the rule identifier and an <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsElement> array containing a <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf> object.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="0ae5e-142">Successivamente, l'esempio aggiunge riferimenti a regole per `ruleEurope` e `ruleSAmerica` dalla regola `WorldCupWinner`.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="0ae5e-142">Subsequently, the example adds rule references to `ruleEurope` and `ruleSAmerica` from the rule `WorldCupWinner`.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
public void WorldSoccerWinners ()  
{  
  // Create a grammar from an SRGSDocument, create a new rule  
  // and set its scope to public.  
  SrgsDocument srgsGrammar = new SrgsDocument ();  
  SrgsRule winnerRule = new SrgsRule ("WorldCupWinner");  
  winnerRule.Scope = SrgsRuleScope.Public;  
  
  // Add the introduction.  
  winnerRule.Elements.Add (new SrgsItem ("A nation that has won the world cup is"));  
  
  // Create the rule for the European nations.  
  SrgsOneOf oneOfEurope = new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {new SrgsItem("England"), new SrgsItem("France"), new SrgsItem("Germany"), new SrgsItem("Italy")});  
  SrgsRule ruleEurope = (new SrgsRule("EuropeanNations", new SrgsElement[] {oneOfEurope}));  
  
  // Create the rule for the South American nations.  
  SrgsOneOf oneOfSAmerica = new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {new SrgsItem("Argentina"), new SrgsItem("Brazil"), new SrgsItem("Uruguay")});  
  SrgsRule ruleSAmerica = (new SrgsRule("SouthAmericanNations", new SrgsElement[] {oneOfSAmerica}));  
  
  // Add references to winnerRule for ruleEurope and ruleSAmerica.  
  winnerRule.Elements.Add(new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {(new SrgsItem (new SrgsRuleRef(ruleEurope))), new SrgsItem(new SrgsRuleRef(ruleSAmerica))}));  
  
  // Add all the rules to the grammar and make winnerRule  
  // the root rule of the grammar.  
  document.Rules.Add(new SrgsRule[] {winnerRule, ruleEurope, ruleSAmerica});  
  srgsGrammar.Root = winnerRule;  
}  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="0ae5e-143">La grammatica creata ha il formato seguente.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="0ae5e-143">The created grammar has the following form.</span></span>  
  
```xml  
<grammar version="1.0" xml:lang="en-US" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2001/06/grammar" root="WorldCupWinner">  
    <rule id="WorldCupWinner" scope="public">  
        <item> A nation that has won the world cup is </item>  
        <one-of>  
            <item>  
                <ruleref uri="#EuropeanNations" />  
            </item>  
            <item>  
                <ruleref uri="#SouthAmericanNations" />  
            </item>  
        </one-of>  
    </rule>  
    <rule id="EuropeanNations">  
        <one-of>  
            <item> England </item>  
            <item> France </item>  
            <item> Germany </item>  
            <item> Italy </item>  
        </one-of>  
    </rule>  
    <rule id="SouthAmericanNations">  
        <one-of>  
            <item> Argentina </item>  
            <item> Brazil </item>  
            <item> Uruguay </item>  
        </one-of>  
    </rule>  
</grammar>  
```

  
  
## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="0ae5e-150">Tipiche aggiunte a un <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule> oggetto includere <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsItem>, <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf>, <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRuleRef>, e <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken> oggetti che specificano ciò che è possono dire relatori.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="0ae5e-150">Typical additions to an <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule> object include <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsItem>, <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf>, <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRuleRef>, and <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken> objects that specify what speakers can say.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="0ae5e-151">Un elemento di regola valida deve contenere almeno una parte del testo riconoscibile o un riferimento a una regola.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="0ae5e-151">A valid rule element must contain at least one piece of recognizable text or one rule reference.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="0ae5e-152">Visualizzare [creare grammatiche usando SrgsGrammar](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/e4d9f96e-2241-4c39-b9e0-ac9ef4e9a906) per altre informazioni.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="0ae5e-152">See [Create Grammars Using SrgsGrammar](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/e4d9f96e-2241-4c39-b9e0-ac9ef4e9a906) for more information.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="0ae5e-153">Un' <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule> oggetto può anche contenere <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsNameValueTag> e <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsSemanticInterpretationTag> gli oggetti che aggiungono semantiche chiavi e valori semantici per la regola.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="0ae5e-153">An <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule> object may also contain <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsNameValueTag> and <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsSemanticInterpretationTag> objects that add semantic values and semantic keys to the rule.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="0ae5e-154">Il motore di riconoscimento vocale restituisce le informazioni semantiche, nonché la frase riconosciuta, quando riconosce la frase.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="0ae5e-154">The speech recognition engine will return the semantic information, as well as the recognized phrase, when it recognizes the phrase.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="0ae5e-155">Visualizzare [Markup interpretazione semantica](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/2e115391-73b3-4666-8fd1-540c529de3b0) per altre informazioni.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="0ae5e-155">See [Semantic Interpretation Markup](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/2e115391-73b3-4666-8fd1-540c529de3b0) for more information.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="0ae5e-156">L'esempio seguente crea una grammatica che riconosce la frase "è un nazione che ha vinto del mondo FIFA" seguito dal nome di un paese ha vinto del mondo FIFA.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="0ae5e-156">The following example creates a grammar that recognizes the phrase "A nation that has won the World Cup is" followed by the name of a country that has won the World Cup.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="0ae5e-157">Dopo aver creato il <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule> oggetto `winnerRule` e assegnando l'identificatore di stringa `WorldCupWinner`, nell'esempio viene usato il <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule.Add%2A> metodo a cui aggiungere la stringa "è un nazione che ha vinto del mondo FIFA" per la regola.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="0ae5e-157">After creating the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule> object `winnerRule` and giving it the string identifier `WorldCupWinner`, the example uses the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule.Add%2A> method to append the string  "A nation that has won the World Cup is" to the rule.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="0ae5e-158">Nell'esempio vengono quindi create due regole aggiuntive `ruleEurope` e `ruleSAmerica`.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="0ae5e-158">The example then creates two additional rules, `ruleEurope` and  `ruleSAmerica`.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="0ae5e-159">Usando il <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule.Add%2A> metodo, l'esempio aggiunge un <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf> dell'oggetto per il `WorldCupWinner` regola contenente riferimenti a regole per `ruleEurope` e `ruleSAmerica`.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="0ae5e-159">Again using the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule.Add%2A> method, the example appends an <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf> object to the `WorldCupWinner` rule that contains rule references to `ruleEurope` and `ruleSAmerica`.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
// Create an SrgsDocument, create a new rule  
// and set its scope to public.  
SrgsDocument document = new SrgsDocument();  
SrgsRule winnerRule = new SrgsRule("WorldCupWinner");  
winnerRule.Scope = SrgsRuleScope.Public;  
  
// Add the introduction.  
winnerRule.Elements.Add(new SrgsItem("A nation that has won the world cup is: "));  
  
// Create the rule for the European nations.  
SrgsOneOf oneOfEurope = new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {new SrgsItem("England"), new SrgsItem("France"), new SrgsItem("Germany"), new SrgsItem("Italy")});  
SrgsRule ruleEurope = (new SrgsRule("EuropeanNations", new SrgsElement[] {oneOfEurope}));  
  
// Create the rule for the South American nations.  
SrgsOneOf oneOfSAmerica = new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {new SrgsItem("Argentina"), new SrgsItem("Brazil"), new SrgsItem("Uruguay")});  
SrgsRule ruleSAmerica = (new SrgsRule("SouthAmericanNations", new SrgsElement[] {oneOfSAmerica}));  
  
// Add references to winnerRule for ruleEurope and ruleSAmerica.  
winnerRule.Elements.Add(new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {(new SrgsItem (new SrgsRuleRef(ruleEurope))), new SrgsItem(new SrgsRuleRef(ruleSAmerica))}));  
  
// Add all the rules to the document and make winnerRule   
// the root rule of the document.  
document.Rules.Add(new SrgsRule[] {winnerRule, ruleEurope, ruleSAmerica});  
document.Root = winnerRule;  
```

  
  
## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="0ae5e-186">Il valore predefinito per l'ambito è `Private`.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="0ae5e-186">The default value for scope is `Private`.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="0ae5e-187">Una regola privata può essere attivata solo per il riconoscimento da un riferimento di regola da una regola radice nella grammatica contenitore o da un'altra regola di cui viene fatto riferimento dalla regola radice.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="0ae5e-187">A private rule can only be activated for recognition by a rule reference from the root rule in its containing grammar or from another rule that is referenced from the root rule.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="0ae5e-188">Impossibile fare riferimento a una regola privata da una grammatica esterna, a meno che la regola privata è dichiarata come la regola radice della grammatica contenitore.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="0ae5e-188">A private rule cannot be referenced by an external grammar, unless the private rule is declared as the root rule of its containing grammar.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="0ae5e-189">Se il relativo ambito è impostato su `Public`, un' <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule> oggetto può essere attivato per il riconoscimento da un riferimento da un <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRuleRef> oggetto nella grammatica contenitore o da una regola in una grammatica esterna.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="0ae5e-189">If its scope is set to `Public`, an <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule> object can be activated for recognition by a reference from a <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRuleRef> object in the containing grammar or from a rule in an external grammar.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="0ae5e-190">L'esempio seguente crea una grammatica che riconosce la frase "è un nazione che ha vinto del mondo FIFA" seguito dal nome di un paese ha vinto del mondo FIFA.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="0ae5e-190">The following example creates a grammar that recognizes the phrase "A nation that has won the World Cup is" followed by the name of a country that has won the World Cup.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="0ae5e-191">Crea una regola pubblica denominata `WorldCupWinner` e imposta l'ambito della regola al pubblico.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="0ae5e-191">It creates a public rule named `WorldCupWinner` and sets the scope of that rule to Public.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
// Create an SrgsDocument, create a new rule and set its scope to public.  
SrgsDocument document = new SrgsDocument();  
SrgsRule winnerRule = new SrgsRule("WorldCupWinner");  
winnerRule.Scope = SrgsRuleScope.Public;  
  
// Add the introduction.  
winnerRule.Elements.Add(new SrgsItem("A nation that has won the world cup is: "));  
  
// Create the rule for the European nations.  
SrgsOneOf oneOfEurope = new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {new SrgsItem("England"), new SrgsItem("France"), new SrgsItem("Germany"), new SrgsItem("Italy")});  
SrgsRule ruleEurope = (new SrgsRule("EuropeanNations", new SrgsElement[] {oneOfEurope}));  
  
// Create the rule for the South American nations.  
SrgsOneOf oneOfSAmerica = new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {new SrgsItem("Argentina"), new SrgsItem("Brazil"), new SrgsItem("Uruguay")});  
SrgsRule ruleSAmerica = (new SrgsRule("SouthAmericanNations", new SrgsElement[] {oneOfSAmerica}));  
  
// Add references to winnerRule for ruleEurope and ruleSAmerica.  
winnerRule.Elements.Add(new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {(new SrgsItem (new SrgsRuleRef(ruleEurope)), new SrgsItem(new SrgsRuleRef(ruleSAmerica)})));  
  
// Add all the rules to the document and make winnerRule   
// the root rule of the document.  
document.Rules.Add(new SrgsRule[] {winnerRule, ruleEurope, ruleSAmerica});  
document.Root = winnerRule;  
```  
  
